metatags.dc.title: Function
metatags.dc.creator: Weisstein, Eric W.
metatags.dc.description: A function is a relation that uniquely associates members of one set with members of another set. More formally, a function from A to B is an object f such that every a in A is uniquely associated with an object f(a) in B. A function is therefore a many-to-one (or sometimes one-to-one) relation.
